using a custom GenericArrayType in tests without reflection would be considered direct access. That’s a bit confusing!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_v7usnBFoNAScYJS6ZsuiDYaz|fc_000de0be998528f4016a0193e8b318819ebaa557ec34d03a4f\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"grep -R \\\"removeMixIn\\\\|addMixIn\\\" -n /home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/source_context/com.alibaba/fastjson/1.2.83/main/extracted/com/alibaba/fastjson/JSON.java | head -20\"}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 762, \"output\": 1069, \"cacheRead\": 22528, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 24359, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1778488276761, \"responseId\": \"resp_000de0be998528f4016a0193d5466c819ead19f7cc3d1f3f10\"}}\nhuman-intervention-logs/com.alibaba:fastjson:1.2.83/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-11T08-34-58-870473Z.log:2044:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Evaluating dependencies for JAXB**\\n\\nI’m considering whether I need to add dependencies for jaxb since JDK21 does not include javax.xml.bind. Should I include test dependencies? For the isXmlField Class.forName with the javax.xml.bind annotation, I might need the jaxb-api. Hibernate could also be added, but the rule states that tests should be outside library packages. If I create a helper package for org.hibernate in tests, it may complicate things. I wonder if adding hibernate-core is too heavy, or if I should create a test source instead. It's tricky!\\n\\n**Clarifying test file structure**\\n\\nThis suggests having only one test file for each class, but what about helper classes? It says to maintain coverage in dedicated Java test files. Maybe I could use nested classes